<br>
1. Most certainly. If you're good with bolts, Seeking Flame and Shock of Steel are your tickets to raw damage at 59. Don't forget that Banishment eats a Star Ruby and has a reuse timer of 2 minutes.<br>
<br>
2. Pre-60, you want (in order of preference) Epic, 60 Water, or 59 Air. Post 60, 62 Water, 61 Air, Epic.<br>
<br>
3. None that I've seen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 2:50:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mages and Trials in PoP.....</span><hr size=1> Dont use shock of steel, use blaze (preferably sofb + 61 bolt), mr based spells are resisted much more than fire ones.<br>
<br>
Banishment isnt that great, dont think you *have* to have it - it seems to be resisted about 50% of the time unless the mob is already tashed/malaed &amp; when it does, youre kinda screwed since the mob will come for you most of the time which means you have to kite it instead of nuking more.  Plus, banishment is 500 mana, which means = lotta wasted mana if you get resisted.  Its great when it works, but if you are planning on relying on it to get you through, well you &amp; your group is going to have issues.<br>
<br>
If you have boots of bladecalling, use them once on the 1st mob of each round, since you have longer to kill that mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aamilae>Aamilae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 424<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 3:06:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mages and Trials in PoP.....</span><hr size=1> For groups that are not the best equipped mages make doing the trials far more possible than any other class, simply because we add a ton of dps.<br>
<br>
I personally have found Shock of Steel to be a wonderful spell in the various trials, but atm I'm 62 -- of course levels will vary your mileage.  The reason I use it over SoFB is that while it is resisted more often, I can do more damage per mana with it than SoFB.  The Trials themselves are heavily based on mana usage, especially for the under-equipped magician -- like myself.<br>
<br>
Don't forget group DS, don't bother debuffing and pick a beefy pet unless your tanks and enchanter are just that good.  Losing a pet in the middle of a trial hurts mana.  Also, pickup a vog or something similiar since more than likely the trial may last longer than burnout does :)<br>
<br>
<br>
